OK. So I've pretty much only had to spend a handful of skill points, since everything so far has gone up on its own through practice. The need for weapon skill debate aside, I let 1H blunt and piercing take care of themselves against blues, and of course all of the spell skills, med, offense and defense go up on their own too.<br>
<br>
So what am I saving them for? From what I understand, if I opt for a trade skill I can do low-level combines to drive that up, and there is the new offshoot to research to drive that up without burning the expensive scroll research components.<br>
<br>
So how should I be saving them?<br>
<br>
